# No assumed short circuits — seek clarification

These instructions are for the **AI assistant**, not as a user reminder.

- When requirements are ambiguous, **do not** infer that the user wants **copper or preview
  lines that would short-circuit** separate nets (e.g. one continuous trace tying many pads on
  a row/column, bus lines across unrelated holes, or same-layer paths that imply unintended
  connectivity).

- **Stop and ask for clarification** rather than producing artwork that **short circuits**
  the real electrical intent.

- Informal wording is **not** permission to merge nets on a layer. If unsure whether a path
  would create a **short circuit** between distinct signals, **ask first**.

- This applies especially to **PCB geometry**, **layer discipline**, **preview SVG**, and
  **EasyEDA / copper** in this repo. See `docs/adapter-routing-invariants.md`.
